olive oil
1 carrot
1 pear
½ tin sweetcorn
1 packet beef strips
1 packet cornflour
1 packet Korean Stir-Fry Sauce
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet ponzu sauce
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet sriracha
1 packet mayonnaise

• Grate carrot. Thinly slice pear. Drain sweetcorn.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef strips and cornflour. Set aside.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook sweetcorn, tossing, until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the corn kernels are "popping" out.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips, tossing, in batches until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Add Korean stir-fry sauce and cook, stirring, until coated and heated through, 1 minute.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• Meanwhile, combine shredded cabbage mix to the charred corn, along with pear, carrot, ponzu sauce and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.
• In a small bowl, combine sriracha, mayonnaise and a dash of water. Season to taste.

• Divide charred corn slaw between bowls. Top with Korean-style sesame beef.
• Drizzle with sriracha mayo to serve. Enjoy!